ENERC(kJ) (original): energy, total metabolizable; calculated from the energy-producing food components (original as from source)
XN: Conversion factor to calculate total protein from nitrogen
PROTCNT(g): Protein, total; calculated from total nitrogen
PROTCNP(g): Protein, total; calculated from protein nitrogen
PROT-(g): Protein, total; method of determination unknown or variable
FATCE(g): Fat, total; derived by analysis using continuous extraction
FAT-(g): Fat; method of determination unknown or mixed methods
CHOAVLM(g): Carbohydrate, available; expressed in monosaccharide equivalents
CHO-(g): carbohydrate; method of determination unknown or variable
SUGARM(g): Sugars, total; expressed in monosaccharide equivalents
STARCHM(g): Starch, available; expressed in monosaccharide equivalents
FIBTG(g): fibre, total dietary; determined gravimetrically by the AOAC total dietary fibre method (Prosky and similar methods)
FIBTS(g) Southgate: Fibre, total dietary; Southgate colorimetric procedure
FIB-(g): Fibre; method of determination unknown or variable
FIBND(g): Fibre; determined by neutral detergent method
FIBAD(g): Fibre; determined by acid detergent method
VITA_RAE(mcg): vitamin A retinol activity equivalent (RAE); calculated by summation of the vitamin A activities of retinol and the active carotenoids
VITA(mcg): Vitamin A; calculated by summation of the vitamin A activities of retinol and the active carotenoids
VITD-(mcg): Vitamin D, method unknown or variable
VITE(mg): vitamin E; calculated by summation of the vitamin E activities of the active tocopherols and tocotrienols; expressed as alpha-tocopherol equivalents
VITE-(mg): Vitamin E; method unknown or variable; expressed as alpha-tocopherol equivalents
VITB6A(mg): Vitamin B-6, total; determined by analysis
VITB6C(mg): Vitamin B-6, total; calculated by summation
VITB6-(mg): Vitamin B6, method unknown or variable
FOLSUM(mcg): Sum of folate vitamers determined by HPLC
FOLFD(mcg): Folate food, naturally occuring food folates
XFA (internal use): fatty acid conversion factor for internal use
PHYTCPPI(mg): phytic acid, determined by indirect preciptation
PHYTCPPD(mg): phytic acid, determined by direct preciptation
PHYTCPP(mg): phytic acid, calc. from phytate phosphorus, anion exchange method
PHYTC-(mg): phytic acid, calc. from phytate phosphorus, method unk.
PPI(mg): phytate phosphorus, determined by indirect preciptation
PPD(mg): phytate phosphorus, determined by direct preciptation
IPSUM (mg): total inositol phosphates (sum of all fractions)
